---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base title="Crontinel Agent - Connect Your Server">
    <main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-16">
        <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Connect Your Server - Crontinel Agent</h1>
        <p class="text-slate-400 mb-8">Install the Crontinel agent on your server to receive and execute cloud-triggered commands.</p>

        <section class="mb-12">
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-3">What is the Agent?</h2>
            <p class="text-slate-400 mb-4">The Crontinel agent is a lightweight daemon that runs on your server, connects to app.crontinel.com via SSE, and listens for commands. When you schedule a trigger from the cloud, the agent receives it, executes it, reports the result, and it appears in your dashboard.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-12">
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-3">Laravel Agent</h2>
            <div class="bg-slate-900 rounded-xl p-5 mb-4">
                <pre class="text-sm text-green-400 overflow-x-auto"><code># 1. Install the package
composer require crontinel/laravel

# 2. Run the install command
php artisan crontinel:install

# 3. Add to .env
CRONTINEL_API_KEY=YOUR_API_KEY_HERE
CRONTINEL_API_URL=https://app.crontinel.com

# 4. Start the agent
php artisan crontinel:agent</code></pre>
            </div>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-500">Generate systemd or Supervisor config: <code class="text-green-400">php artisan crontinel:agent --systemd</code></p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-12">
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-3">Node.js Agent</h2>
            <div class="bg-slate-900 rounded-xl p-5 mb-4">
                <pre class="text-sm text-green-400 overflow-x-auto"><code># 1. Install
npm install @crontinel/node

# 2. Set env vars
export CRONTINEL_API_KEY=YOUR_API_KEY_HERE
export CRONTINEL_APP_ID=your-app-slug

# 3. Start the agent
npx crontinel agent</code></pre>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-12">
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-3">Python Agent</h2>
            <div class="bg-slate-900 rounded-xl p-5 mb-4">
                <pre class="text-sm text-green-400 overflow-x-auto"><code># Install from source (PyPI pending)
git clone https://github.com/crontinel/python.git
cd python
pip install -e .

# Set env vars
export CRONTINEL_API_KEY=YOUR_API_KEY_HERE
export CRONTINEL_APP_ID=your-app-slug

# Start the agent
crontinel agent</code></pre>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-12">
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-3">Test Your Agent</h2>
            <p class="text-slate-400 mb-4">Schedule a trigger to verify the agent is connected:</p>
            <div class="bg-slate-900 rounded-xl p-5">
                <pre class="text-sm text-green-400 overflow-x-auto"><code>curl -X POST https://app.crontinel.com/api/v1/triggers \
  -H "X-API-Key: YOUR_API_KEY" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '&#123;"app_id": 1, "command": "echo hello", "schedule": "now"&#125;'</code></pre>
            </div>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 mt-3">Check the <strong class="text-white">Trigger history</strong> section on your app page to see the result.</p>
        </section>
    </main>
</Base>
